# The Cortex — Coding Rules

## Language & Framework

- TypeScript strict mode. No `any` types. Use explicit return types on exported functions.
- React 18+ with functional components only. No class components.
- Vite 7 as build tool. Config in `vite.config.ts`.
- Path alias `@/` maps to `src/`. Always use `@/` imports for cross-directory references.

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS v4 with custom `@theme` in `src/index.css`. No separate `tailwind.config` file.
- Dark mode is the only mode. Background is `bg-surface-dark` (#020617). Panels use `bg-surface-panel` (#0f172a).
- Use the `.glass-panel` and `.glass-panel-sm` utility classes for translucent containers. Do not recreate backdrop-blur inline.
- Neon color tokens: `neon-blue`, `neon-purple`, `neon-pink`, `neon-green`, `neon-cyan`. Use with Tailwind opacity modifiers (e.g. `text-neon-blue`, `border-neon-purple/30`, `bg-neon-green/10`).
- Typography: `font-mono` for data/code/labels, `font-sans` (Inter) for body text.
- Keep all custom keyframes and CSS utilities in `src/index.css`, not in component files.

## State Management

- Zustand single store in `src/store/useInterviewStore.ts`. No other state libraries.
- Use selector functions to subscribe to specific slices: `useInterviewStore((s) => s.messages)`.
- Do not access the store outside React components except via `useInterviewStore.getState()`.

## Animation

- Framer Motion for all entrance/exit/layout animations on React components.
- Use `motion.div` (or `motion.span`, etc.) with `initial`, `animate`, `exit`, and `transition` props.
- Prefer spring physics (`type: "spring"`) for interactive/entrance animations.
- Use CSS keyframe animations (defined in index.css) for continuous ambient effects (pulse, glow, breathe).

## React Flow (Blueprint)

- Custom node components live in `src/components/Blueprint/nodes/`.
- Custom edge components live in `src/components/Blueprint/edges/`.
- Node types are registered as a stable object outside the component (not inside render). Same for edge types.
- Each custom node accepts a `delay` prop in `data` for staggered build-sequence animation.
- Do not use default React Flow node styling. Override with glassmorphism.

## Component Organization

- Group related components into feature directories: `NeuralStream/`, `HUD/`, `Blueprint/`, `Compilation/`.
- One component per file. Named exports for components, default export only for `App.tsx`.
- Hooks go in `src/hooks/`. Store goes in `src/store/`.
- Prefer `memo()` for React Flow node/edge components.

## Code Style

- Use `const` by default. Use `let` only when reassignment is needed.
- Arrow functions for inline callbacks. Named `function` declarations for exported components and hooks.
- Destructure props in function parameters.
- Keep components under 150 lines. Extract sub-components or hooks if larger.
- No `console.log` in committed code.

## API Integration

- TanStack Query (React Query) for all async data fetching and mutations.
- API client lives in `src/api/client.ts`. Types in `src/api/types.ts`.
- Use `useAgent()` hook in components — it currently defaults to mock mode for demo consistency.
- Do not call `fetch()` or `axios` directly in components. Always go through the API client.
- The ONLY frontend env var is `VITE_API_URL`.

## Composite Dashboard (`DashboardUI`)

- The app uses a semantic interpreter to render composite dashboards from internal mock payloads.
- `SemanticInterpreter` iterates components, rendering each archetype with `RadarReveal`.
- Layout uses CSS Grid: `PROCESS_TOPOLOGY` / `KNOWLEDGE_DOCUMENT` = `col-span-full`. Cards = `col-span-1` in 2-col grid.
- `RadarReveal` animates in 3 phases: neon scan line → vertical expand → content fade-in. Stagger: `delayMs={index * 400}`.
- `SupplyTable` maps `UIEntity` fields: `name`, `type`, `description`.
- `MarkdownRenderer` uses `react-markdown`.

## Personas & Agent Team Loader

- The app simulates agent fan-out during processing.
- `AgentTeamLoader` renders animated persona icons during the active phase.
- Config in `PersonaConfig`: MECHANIC (Wrench/amber), TECH_WRITER (BookOpen/blue), LOGISTICS (Truck/emerald), AUDITOR (ShieldCheck/red), PROCESS_ENGINEER (Network/purple).

## Do Not

- Do not install additional CSS frameworks (no styled-components, no CSS modules, no Emotion).
- Do not call backend APIs directly from components. Use the hooks in `src/hooks/`.
- Do not use `useEffect` for state synchronization that can be derived. Use Zustand selectors or `useMemo`.
- Do not put business logic in components. Extract to hooks or utility functions.
- Do not hardcode API URLs. Use environment variables via `import.meta.env`.
- **NEVER put API keys, secrets, or internal service URLs in the frontend.**

## React Flow → BPMN Mapping
- React Flow node type `logic` maps to BPMN gateways. Node types `trigger` and `action` map to BPMN tasks.
- The canvas uses `useMockWorkflowBuilder` to generate the graph in mock mode.
- `ActionNode` displays a glassmorphism semantic HUD tooltip on hover showing metadata.
